Along the quiet path to a dusty village, four families among the crowd agreed to form a group led by Ley P., 30, who is a mother of two children, both students. Married to Chhouk, 33, a fisherman along the Mekong River, Ley awakes early every morning to fish and then hurries to the market to sell her catch, sometH. she has done since 2000. She now wants to increase her income and so is requesting a loan to buy more fisH. nets for the family's business. 

The other group members, all of whom live in Siem Reap Province, Cambodia, are: 

Eng T., 32, who sells groceries in front of her house and is looking for a loan to invest in her business;

Nee M., 28, who sells dessert in the market and is requesting a loan to decorate her house;

Eang H., 21, who sells fish in the market and is seeking a loan to buy more fisH. nets for her family's business.
